# Project Structure

The project follows a standard Astro structure with Storyblok integration:

## Main Directories

- [src/](mdc:src) - Main source code
  - [src/pages/](mdc:src/pages) - Astro pages that define routes
  - [src/components/](mdc:src/components) - Reusable components (non-Storyblok)
  - [src/storyblok/](mdc:src/storyblok) - Storyblok components that map to CMS blocks
  - [src/layouts/](mdc:src/layouts) - Page layouts used as templates
  - [src/styles/](mdc:src/styles) - CSS and Tailwind styling
  - [src/utils/](mdc:src/utils) - Utility functions and helpers
  - [src/lib/](mdc:src/lib) - Library code and third-party integrations
  - [src/types/](mdc:src/types) - TypeScript type definitions
  - [src/scripts/](mdc:src/scripts) - Client-side scripts

## Build and Output Directories

- [.astro/](mdc:.astro) - Astro build cache
- [dist/](mdc:dist) - Built output ready for deployment
- [public/](mdc:public) - Static assets served as-is

## Configuration Files

- [astro.config.mjs](mdc:astro.config.mjs) - Astro configuration including Storyblok setup
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration
- [.prettierrc](mdc:.prettierrc) - Code formatting rules
- [components.json](mdc:components.json) - Component configuration
